# Docker command cheatsheet

All PHP runtime lives in the `app` container. The WSL host has no working PHP for FreeCRM.

- PHP script:     `docker compose exec -T app php <path>`
- Composer:       `docker compose exec -T app composer <cmd>`
- Cron task:      `docker compose exec -T app php cron/vtigercron.php service=LBL_<NAME>`
- Tail logs (host): `tail -f cache/logs/system.log` (also `cron.log`)
- Clear Smarty cache: `rm -f cache/templates_c/*.php`

**Database queries:** use the `freecrm-mysql` MCP server — not Docker shell. See `mcp-database-access.mdc`.

MariaDB shell (manual debugging only, when user asks or MCP is down):
`docker compose exec -T db mariadb -ufreecrm -pfreecrm freecrm`
